## Self-Update Preflight

- **Source checkout:** `${AGENTS_SYSTEM_SETUP_HOME:-$HOME/github/agents-system-setup}`.
- **Status:** {{SELF_UPDATE_PREFLIGHT_STATUS}}  <!-- checked | already-current | ff-updated | requires-human | skipped -->
- **Evidence / question:** {{SELF_UPDATE_PREFLIGHT_EVIDENCE}}.
- **Policy:** fast-forward only when the checkout exists, is a Git worktree, is clean, has an upstream, `git fetch` succeeds, the branch is only behind upstream, and `git merge --ff-only` succeeds.
- **Human-needed cases:** missing checkout, dirty worktree, missing upstream, local-only commits, divergence, fetch failure, plugin-manager ambiguity, or any update that would edit runtime settings.
- **No side effects:** preflight never edits MCP config, plugin/runtime settings, generated agents, memory files, or release/version metadata.

## Human Input / Question Protocol

| Runtime | Native question surface | Allowlist / config rule | Non-interactive or child-agent fallback |
|---|---|---|---|
{{HUMAN_INPUT_PROVIDER_ROWS}}

- **Fallback schema:** subagents and restricted child agents return one `question_request` to `@orchestrator` when they cannot ask directly.
- **Required fields:** `id`, `asked_by`, `reason`, `question`, optional `choices`, `default`, `urgency`, `if_unanswered`, and concise `context`.
- **Non-terminating flow:** the orchestrator asks once through the provider-native mechanism when available, records the answer/default in the plan and todos, then re-delegates or stops before sensitive writes per `if_unanswered`.
- **Separate gates:** approvals, MCP config writes, artifact-tracking choices, provider memory/hooks, and learning overwrites remain separate approval gates. A question answer is evidence, not blanket approval.
- **Provider safety:** do not invent question-tool names. Copilot custom-agent `tools:` profiles must not include `ask_user`; Codex agent TOML must not include question or memory fields.

## Memory & Learning System

- **Memory profile:** {{LEARNING_MEMORY_PROFILE}}  <!-- project-tracked | project-local | personal-global | disabled -->
- **Native learning surface:** {{NATIVE_LEARNING_SURFACE}}  <!-- documented-only | approved-native-config | none -->
- **Memory owner:** {{LEARNING_MEMORY_OWNER}}  <!-- @orchestrator or @memory-steward -->
- **Curated memory path:** {{LEARNING_MEMORY_PATH}}
- **Operational ledger:** {{LEARNING_LEDGER_PATH}}  <!-- append-only JSONL/DB when enabled; never Markdown inside runtime agents/ dirs -->
- **Update policy:** overwrite requires orchestrator approval; supersede old lessons instead of silently deleting them.
- **Safety:** no secrets or raw credentials in learnings; summarize and link evidence instead of storing raw logs. Sensitive new learnings require orchestrator and security-owner approval when tagged `risk` or when they mention MCP, CI/release, dependencies, secrets, or generated scripts.
- **Native vs plugin-managed:** provider-native memory is complementary and must be enabled only by its own approval path. The plugin-managed Learning Check stays active and cannot silently change MCP, hooks, plugin settings, artifact tracking, or learning-overwrite gates.
- **Load rule:** read the Learning Index first, then only entries matching the task category, path, runtime, or tool.
- **Learning Check:** before final response, report `Learning Check: none | proposed_new:<id> | proposed_update:<id> | deferred:<reason>`.

See `{{LEARNING_MEMORY_REFERENCE}}` for the full memory schema, storage profiles, and hook policy.

### Task-Type Routing Map

Use this table to decide which references each agent loads beyond `AGENTS.md` Read First. The orchestrator picks the task tag and surfaces it in the Task Assignment so subagents can short-circuit. Use the [Plan Handoff Contract](#plan-handoff-contract) below for the per-tag Recommended Packet Form (short-form vs full-form).

| Task tag | Always load | Load when applicable | Safe to skip | Recommended packet form |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| `read-only-research` | Read First, Directory Architecture | Topology if topology questions | Security & Audit detail, Threat Model long rationale | short-form |
| `requirements-triage` | Read First, Directory Architecture, Human Input / Question Protocol | Security/Audit rows, runtime/platform refs, topology, prior plan only when relevant | Source files outside requested scope, full marketplace research | short-form intake brief |
| `content-quality-review` | Read First, Content Quality, Directory Architecture | Output Contract, Handoff, runtime/platform refs for generated artifacts | Source implementation files unrelated to generated prose | short-form quality signals |
| `code-edit` | Read First, Directory Architecture, owning agent boundary | Quality Gates row for this path | Marketplace research, full platform schemas | short-form (≤2 files) · full-form when >2 files or shared boundary |
| `security-write` | Security & Audit Matrix, Threat Model, owning agent boundary | Security/Audit reference rows for the change | Long marketplace candidate research | full-form |
| `mcp-write` | MCP approval gate, Security & Audit Matrix | Plugin/MCP rendering reference | Architecture Decisions detail | full-form |
| `replication` | Replication contract, Plan Handoff Contract, Output Contract | Models reference for explicit overrides | Project-specific quality gate detail | full-form |
| `release` | Quality Gates, manifests, version sync rules | Runtime update audit | Long architecture rationale | full-form |
| `docs-only` | Read First | Quality Gates only if doc CI exists | Security/MCP gates unless docs touch credentials | short-form |
| `bug-fix` | Read First, Directory Architecture, owning agent boundary | Quality Gates row, repro logs, related ADRs | Long marketplace research | full-form (Reproduction block required) |
| `learning-check` | Memory & Learning System, Learning Index | Detailed learning entry when category/path matches | Full operational ledger, unrelated learnings | short-form |

### Context Freshness

If `AGENTS.md` was already loaded this turn, prefer `Context freshness: recent` in delegated packets so subagents skip the row-by-row reload and read only the rows for the current task tag.

